{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_100","type":"agent_message","text":"Implemented US-008 end-to-end and committed as:\n\n`7ebab44`  \n`feat: US-008 - LlmClient trait and LlmError taxonomy`\n\n### What changed\n- Replaced `ProviderPort` with `LlmClient` in `ports`:\n  - `complete(&self, req: LlmRequest) -> Result<LlmResponse, LlmError>`\n  - `stream(&self, req: LlmRequest) -> Result<Pin<Box<dyn Stream<Item = Result<StreamEvent, LlmError>> + Send>>, LlmError>`\n- Added full `LlmError` taxonomy in `crates/ports/src/provider.rs`:\n  - `AuthError(String)`\n  - `RateLimited { retry_after_ms: Option<u64> }`\n  - `ModelNotAvailable(String)`\n  - `RequestTooLarge(String)`\n  - `InvalidResponse(String)`\n  - `StreamInterrupted(String)`\n  - `Network(String)`\n  - `Timeout(Duration)`\n  - `ProviderError { status: u16, message: String }`\n- Migrated downstream consumers (`application`, `tools`, `bootstrap`, `cli`, `cron`, `provider`) to `LlmClient`/`Llm*` types.\n- Removed duplicate provider-local contract surface (`crates/provider/src/contracts.rs`) so contract is anchored in `ports`.\n- Added contract test: `crates/ports/tests/llm_client_contract.rs`.\n- Updated governance test to require `LlmClient` in `crates/ports/`.\n\n### Policy rule\n- App/services now consume typed `LlmError` instead of raw provider error formats; provider HTTP mapping stays inside provider adapters/clients.\n\n### Verification\n- `cargo fmt --check` ✅\n- `cargo clippy --workspace -- -D warnings` ✅\n- `cargo test --workspace` ✅\n\n<promise>COMPLETE</promise>"}}
